Text: A day has 24 hours, and it is too little.
This post will be very chaotic and divided into a few parts or only two: ).
When I woke up at 5 am today, I had a lot of thoughts in my mind to publish on this post.

Still, finally first thing today was checking how I can prepare HTML code or at least improve what Yoko has made and how to connect with the database, which I had to delete yesterday and build one more time.
After that, I decided that I have to prepare a list of questions to Yoko and Nene for today morning.
That's why the blog is again on the last place.
But I am trying to improve it.
We will have a meeting at 9: 15.

Yoko struggles with her paper and programming in JavaScript, that's why we decided with Nene yesterday (after 3 hours meeting), that I will take this part from Yoko and we have to divide all tasks between two of us.
I really don't know what with Riri.
If she wants to participate or not.
Maybe she will explain it today.
Now will be the pessimistic part.
I am so tired that I am even not frustrated.
At this stage, I have the feeling that we will not finish this project.
We will not achieve what we assumed.
But I decided that it is not essential.
I have too many things on my plate - not only connected with studies.
I can't say to my kids and my husband all the time:  "I have no time for you".
There is also the whole situation in Poland.
More meetings - yes, we should, but from my point of view - if we have not anything concrete, then it does not make sense.
Last week I had spent -literally speaking- 3 days at the lab + a lot of hours at home preparing the first milestone for INFO202.
I am proud of myself because I understand this - at least at some stage with the java programming: )I have huge problems with sequence diagrams - but this was the only part I got lower marks.
I can deal with that: ).
Each of us needs time for herself to prepare some stuff for the project, and I work more efficiently at my home on a strange part of the day or night.
That's it for today, I got to go.
